---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "How to Calculate Your Macros for Weight Loss | SmartFitCalc";
const description =
    "Step-by-step guide to calculating macronutrients for effective weight loss while preserving muscle mass.";

const articleStructuredData = {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    headline: "How to Calculate Your Macros for Weight Loss",
    description: description,
    datePublished: "2024-12-01",
    dateModified: "2025-12-28",
    author: {
        "@type": "Organization",
        name: "SmartFitCalc",
        url: "https://smartfitcalc.com",
    },
    publisher: {
        "@type": "Organization",
        name: "SmartFitCalc",
        url: "https://smartfitcalc.com",
        logo: {
            "@type": "ImageObject",
            url: "https://smartfitcalc.com/favicon.svg",
        },
    },
    mainEntityOfPage: {
        "@type": "WebPage",
        "@id": "https://smartfitcalc.com/blog/calculate-macros-weight-loss",
    },
};
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
    <script
        type="application/ld+json"
        set:html={JSON.stringify(articleStructuredData)}
    />
    <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <header class="mb-10 text-center">
            <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-primary-600 hover:underline"
                >← Back to Blog</a
            >
            <h1 class="mt-4 mb-4 text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-800">
                How to Calculate Your Macros for Weight Loss
            </h1>
            <div class="text-gray-500 text-sm">December 2024 • 7 min read</div>
        </header>

        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-600">
            <p class="lead text-xl">
                Counting macros is one of the most effective approaches to
                weight loss because it focuses on food quality, not just
                quantity. Here's exactly how to set up your macros for optimal
                fat loss.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-4">
                Why Macros Matter for Weight Loss
            </h2>
            <p>
                While calories determine whether you lose or gain weight, <strong
                    >macros determine what kind of weight you lose</strong
                >. Eating the right balance of protein, carbs, and fat helps
                you:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Preserve muscle while losing fat</li>
                <li>Stay fuller on fewer calories</li>
                <li>Maintain energy for workouts</li>
                <li>Keep hormones balanced</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-4">
                Step 1: Calculate Your Calorie Target
            </h2>
            <p>
                Start by finding your TDEE (Total Daily Energy Expenditure)
                using our <a href="/" class="text-primary-600 hover:underline"
                    >calculator</a
                >. For weight loss, subtract 500 calories to create a safe
                deficit that yields about 0.5 kg (1 lb) loss per week.
            </p>
            <div class="rounded-xl bg-gray-50 p-4 my-4 border">
                <p class="font-medium text-gray-800">Example:</p>
                <p>TDEE: 2,400 calories → Weight loss target: 1,900 calories</p>
            </div>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-4">
                Step 2: Set Your Protein
            </h2>
            <p>
                Protein is the most important macro for weight loss. It
                preserves muscle, keeps you full, and burns more calories during
                digestion. For weight loss, aim for:
            </p>
            <div class="rounded-xl bg-red-50 p-4 my-4 border border-red-100">
                <p class="font-bold text-red-800">
                    1.8 - 2.4 grams per kg of body weight
                </p>
                <p class="text-red-700 text-sm mt-1">
                    Example: 80kg person → 144-192g protein daily
                </p>
            </div>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-4">
                Step 3: Set Your Fat
            </h2>
            <p>
                Fat is essential for hormone production and vitamin absorption.
                Don't go too low. Aim for 20-30% of total calories.
            </p>
            <div class="rounded-xl bg-blue-50 p-4 my-4 border border-blue-100">
                <p class="font-bold text-blue-800">
                    0.5 - 1 gram per kg of body weight
                </p>
                <p class="text-blue-700 text-sm mt-1">
                    Example: 80kg person → 40-80g fat daily
                </p>
            </div>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-4">
                Step 4: Fill the Rest with Carbs
            </h2>
            <p>
                After setting protein and fat, the remaining calories go to
                carbs. They fuel your workouts and keep energy levels stable.
            </p>
            <div
                class="rounded-xl bg-amber-50 p-4 my-4 border border-amber-100"
            >
                <p class="font-bold text-amber-800">
                    Remaining calories ÷ 4 = carb grams
                </p>
            </div>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-4">
                Example Macro Calculation
            </h2>
            <p>
                Let's calculate macros for an 80kg person with a 1,900 calorie
                target:
            </p>
            <div class="rounded-xl bg-gray-50 p-5 my-4 border">
                <ul class="space-y-2">
                    <li><strong>Protein:</strong> 160g × 4 = 640 calories</li>
                    <li><strong>Fat:</strong> 60g × 9 = 540 calories</li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Carbs:</strong> (1,900 - 640 - 540) ÷ 4 = 180g
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t">
                    <p class="font-bold">
                        Final macros: 160g protein | 180g carbs | 60g fat
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-4">
                Tips for Success
            </h2>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <strong>Prioritize protein at every meal</strong> - It's the hardest
                    macro to hit
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Weigh your food</strong> - Eyeballing leads to 30-50%
                    errors
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Plan meals in advance</strong> - Pre-log to ensure you
                    hit your targets
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Allow flexibility</strong> - ±5-10g is close enough
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Be patient</strong> - Give it 2-3 weeks before adjusting
                </li>
            </ol>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-4">
                When to Adjust
            </h2>
            <p>
                If you're not losing weight after 2-3 weeks of consistent
                tracking, reduce calories by 100-200. If you're losing faster
                than 1% body weight per week, you may want to eat slightly more
                to preserve muscle.
            </p>

            <p class="mt-8">
                Ready to get your personalized macros? <a
                    href="/macro-calculator"
                    class="text-primary-600 hover:underline font-medium"
                    >Calculate your macros now →</a
                >
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
            <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
                <a
                    href="/blog/understanding-tdee"
                    class="block rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-4 hover:border-primary-300"
                >
                    <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800">
                        Understanding TDEE
                    </h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
                        First step before setting macros
                    </p>
                </a>
                <a
                    href="/blog/calorie-counting-mistakes"
                    class="block rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-4 hover:border-primary-300"
                >
                    <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800">
                        5 Calorie Counting Mistakes
                    </h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
                        Common pitfalls to avoid
                    </p>
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </article>
</BaseLayout>
